The article describes the state of '''[[race relations]] and [[racism]] in a number of countries'''.

Racism of various forms is found in every country on Earth.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://web.amnesty.org/library/index/engACT400202001|publisher = Amnesty International|title = Racism and the administration of justice}}{{dead link|date=March 2013|url=http://web.amnesty.org/library/index/engACT400202001}}</ref> In different countries, the forms that racism takes may be different for historic, cultural, religious, economic or demographic reasons.

Racism is widely condemned throughout the world, with 175 states signatories of the [[International Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Racial Discrimination]] {{as of|2013|3|7|lc=on}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://treaties.un.org/Pages/ViewDetails.aspx?src=TREATY&mtdsg_no=IV-2&chapter=4&lang=en|title=STATUS AS AT : 07-03-2013 05:04:14 EDT : International Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Racial Discrimination|publisher=[[Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights]]}}</ref>

